{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868308842,"sessionID":"ses_28600cab4ffep6L858aRhkgvHB","part":{"id":"prt_d79ffdfca001Q3TaZqNYs6dEuk","messageID":"msg_d79ffb881001sFjUykbywLuZqU","sessionID":"ses_28600cab4ffep6L858aRhkgvHB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775868308823,"end":1775868308841}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868308856,"sessionID":"ses_28600cab4ffep6L858aRhkgvHB","part":{"id":"prt_d79ffe365001MxcljMh4v7iMIA","messageID":"msg_d79ffb881001sFjUykbywLuZqU","sessionID":"ses_28600cab4ffep6L858aRhkgvHB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/valkey.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/valkey.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package store\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \t\"context\"\n21: \t\"encoding/json\"\n22: \t\"fmt\"\n23: \t\"time\"\n24: \n25: \t\"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n26: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n27: )\n28: \n29: // valkeyStore implements Store interface using Valkey backend.\n30: type valkeyStore struct {\n31: \tcli                  valkey.Client\n32: \tsessionPrefix        string\n33: \texpiryIndexKey       string\n34: \tlastActivityIndexKey string\n35: }\n36: \n37: // newValkeyStore creates a new Valkey-backed Store instance.\n38: func newValkeyStore() (Store, error) {\n39: \topts, err := makeValkeyOptions()\n40: \tif err != nil {\n41: \t\treturn nil, err\n42: \t}\n43: \n44: \tclientOption := valkey.ClientOption{\n45: \t\tInitAddress:       opts.InitAddress,\n46: \t\tDisableCache:      opts.DisableCache,\n47: \t\tForceSingleClient: opts.ForceSingleClient,\n48: \t}\n49: \n50: \t// Configure password if provided\n51: \tif opts.Password != \"\" {\n52: \t\tclientOption.Password = opts.Password\n53: \t}\n54: \n55: \tclient, err := valkey.NewClient(clientOption)\n56: \tif err != nil {\n57: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create valkey client: %w\", err)\n58: \t}\n59: \n60: \treturn &valkeyStore{\n61: \t\tcli:                  client,\n62: \t\tsessionPrefix:        sessionPrefix,\n63: \t\texpiryIndexKey:       expiryIndexKey,\n64: \t\tlastActivityIndexKey: lastActivityIndexKey,\n65: \t}, nil\n66: }\n67: \n68: // sessionKey constructs the Valkey key for a session.\n69: func (s *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n70: \treturn s.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n71: }\n72: \n73: // Ping verifies connectivity to the Valkey backend.\n74: // Returns nil on success, error on failure.\n75: func (s *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n76: \tresult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Ping().Build())\n77: \tif result.Error() != nil {\n78: \t\treturn result.Error()\n79: \t}\n80: \n81: \tpong, err := result.ToString()\n82: \tif err != nil {\n83: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse ping response: %w\", err)\n84: \t}\n85: \tif pong != \"PONG\" {\n86: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected ping response: %s\", pong)\n87: \t}\n88: \treturn nil\n89: }\n90: \n91: // GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox info by session ID.\n92: // Returns ErrNotFound if the session does not exist.\n93: func (s *valkeyStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n94: \tif sessionID == \"\" {\n95: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n96: \t}\n97: \n98: \tkey := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n99: \tresult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build())\n100: \tif result.Error() != nil {\n101: \t\tif valkey.IsValkeyNil(result.Error()) {\n102: \t\t\treturn nil, ErrNotFound\n103: \t\t}\n104: \t\treturn nil, result.Error()\n105: \t}\n106: \n107: \tdata, err := result.ToString()\n108: \tif err != nil {\n109: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get session data: %w\", err)\n110: \t}\n111: \n112: \tvar sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n113: \tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\n114: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n115: \t}\n116: \n117: \treturn &sandbox, nil\n118: }\n119: \n120: // StoreSandbox creates a new sandbox entry with atomic index updates.\n121: // Validates sandbox is non-nil and has valid ExpiresAt.\n122: // Uses SETNX to prevent overwriting existing keys.\n123: func (s *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n124: \tif sandbox == nil {\n125: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox is nil\")\n126: \t}\n127: \tif sandbox.SessionID == \"\" {\n128: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n129: \t}\n130: \tif sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n131: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"expiresAt is zero\")\n132: \t}\n133: \n134: \tkey := s.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n135: \tdata, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n136: \tif err != nil {\n137: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n138: \t}\n139: \n140: \tnow := time.Now().Unix()\n141: \n142: \t// Use DoMulti for atomic operations\n143: \tresults := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n144: \t\ts.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Nx().Build(),\n145: \t\ts.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().\n146: \t\t\tScoreMember(float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix()), sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n147: \t\ts.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().\n148: \t\t\tScoreMember(float64(now), sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n149: \t)\n150: \n151: \t// Check for errors in any of the results\n152: \tfor i, r := range results {\n153: \t\tif r.Error() != nil {\n154: \t\t\t// Clean up already executed commands on error (best effort)\n155: \t\t\treturn r.Error()\n156: \t\t}\n157: \n158: \t\t// First command is SET NX - check if it succeeded\n159: \t\tif i == 0 {\n160: \t\t\tsetResult, err := r.ToString()\n161: \t\t\tif err != nil {\n162: \t\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"session already exists\")\n163: \t\t\t}\n164: \t\t\tif setResult != \"OK\" {\n165: \t\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"session already exists\")\n166: \t\t\t}\n167: \t\t}\n168: \t}\n169: \n170: \treturn nil\n171: }\n172: \n173: // UpdateSandbox updates an existing sandbox's JSON data.\n174: // Uses SET with XX flag (key must exist).\n175: // Does NOT modify expiry or last-activity indexes.\n176: func (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n177: \tif sandbox == nil {\n178: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox is nil\")\n179: \t}\n180: \tif sandbox.SessionID == \"\" {\n181: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n182: \t}\n183: \n184: \tkey := s.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n185: \tdata, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n186: \tif err != nil {\n187: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n188: \t}\n189: \n190: \t// SET with XX flag - only set if key exists\n191: \tresult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build())\n192: \tif result.Error() != nil {\n193: \t\treturn result.Error()\n194: \t}\n195: \n196: \t// Check if the operation succeeded (XX returns nil/empty if key doesn't exist)\n197: \tstrResult, err := result.ToString()\n198: \tif err != nil {\n199: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists\")\n200: \t}\n201: \tif strResult != \"OK\" {\n202: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists\")\n203: \t}\n204: \n205: \treturn nil\n206: }\n207: \n208: // DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes a sandbox and its indexes.\n209: // Uses atomic pipeline: DEL + ZREM expiry + ZREM last_activity.\n210: func (s *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n211: \tif sessionID == \"\" {\n212: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n213: \t}\n214: \n215: \tkey := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n216: \n217: \t// Use DoMulti for atomic operations\n218: \tresults := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n219: \t\ts.cli.B().Del().Key(key).Build(),\n220: \t\ts.cli.B().Zrem().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n221: \t\ts.cli.B().Zrem().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n222: \t)\n223: \n224: \t// Check for errors\n225: \tfor _, r := range results {\n226: \t\tif r.Error() != nil {\n227: \t\t\treturn r.Error()\n228: \t\t}\n229: \t}\n230: \n231: \treturn nil\n232: }\n233: \n234: // ListExpiredSandboxes returns sessions with ExpiresAt <= before.\n235: // Queries session:expiry ZSET with ZRANGEBYSCORE.\n236: // Returns nil, nil if limit <= 0.\n237: func (s *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n238: \tif limit <= 0 {\n239: \t\treturn nil, nil\n240: \t}\n241: \n242: \t// Get expired session IDs from the ZSET\n243: \tzrangeResult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).\n244: \t\tMin(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build())\n245: \tif zrangeResult.Error() != nil {\n246: \t\treturn nil, zrangeResult.Error()\n247: \t}\n248: \n249: \tarr, err := zrangeResult.ToArray()\n250: \tif err != nil {\n251: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse zrange result: %w\", err)\n252: \t}\n253: \n254: \tsessionIDs := make([]string, 0, len(arr))\n255: \tfor _, v := range arr {\n256: \t\tid, err := v.ToString()\n257: \t\tif err != nil {\n258: \t\t\tcontinue\n259: \t\t}\n260: \t\tsessionIDs = append(sessionIDs, id)\n261: \t}\n262: \n263: \treturn s.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n264: }\n265: \n266: // ListInactiveSandboxes returns sessions with last activity <= before.\n267: // Queries session:last_activity ZSET with ZRANGEBYSCORE.\n268: // Returns nil, nil if limit <= 0.\n269: func (s *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n270: \tif limit <= 0 {\n271: \t\treturn nil, nil\n272: \t}\n273: \n274: \t// Get inactive session IDs from the ZSET\n275: \tzrangeResult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).\n276: \t\tMin(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build())\n277: \tif zrangeResult.Error() != nil {\n278: \t\treturn nil, zrangeResult.Error()\n279: \t}\n280: \n281: \tarr, err := zrangeResult.ToArray()\n282: \tif err != nil {\n283: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse zrange result: %w\", err)\n284: \t}\n285: \n286: \tsessionIDs := make([]string, 0, len(arr))\n287: \tfor _, v := range arr {\n288: \t\tid, err := v.ToString()\n289: \t\tif err != nil {\n290: \t\t\tcontinue\n291: \t\t}\n292: \t\tsessionIDs = append(sessionIDs, id)\n293: \t}\n294: \n295: \treturn s.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n296: }\n297: \n298: // loadSandboxesBySessionIDs loads sandbox info for the given session IDs.\n299: // Skips entries where the session key is missing (orphaned ZSET entries).\n300: func (s *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n301: \tif len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n302: \t\treturn []*types.SandboxInfo{}, nil\n303: \t}\n304: \n305: \t// Build keys for all session IDs\n306: \tkeys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n307: \tfor i, id := range sessionIDs {\n308: \t\tkeys[i] = s.sessionKey(id)\n309: \t}\n310: \n311: \t// Use MGET to fetch all sessions in one call\n312: \tmgetResult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build())\n313: \tif mgetResult.Error() != nil {\n314: \t\treturn nil, mgetResult.Error()\n315: \t}\n316: \n317: \tarr, err := mgetResult.ToArray()\n318: \tif err != nil {\n319: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse mget result: %w\", err)\n320: \t}\n321: \n322: \t// Parse results, skipping empty entries (orphaned ZSET members)\n323: \tsandboxes := make([]*types.SandboxInfo, 0, len(arr))\n324: \tfor _, v := range arr {\n325: \t\tdata, err := v.ToString()\n326: \t\tif err != nil {\n327: \t\t\t// Nil value or error - skip\n328: \t\t\tcontinue\n329: \t\t}\n330: \n331: \t\tif data == \"\" {\n332: \t\t\t// Orphaned ZSET entry - skip\n333: \t\t\tcontinue\n334: \t\t}\n335: \n336: \t\tvar sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n337: \t\tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\n338: \t\t\t// Failed to parse - skip this entry but continue\n339: \t\t\tcontinue\n340: \t\t}\n341: \n342: \t\tsandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\n343: \t}\n344: \n345: \treturn sandboxes, nil\n346: }\n347: \n348: // UpdateSessionLastActivity updates the last activity timestamp for a session.\n349: // Returns ErrNotFound if session does not exist.\n350: // If at is zero time, uses time.Now().\n351: func (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n352: \tif sessionID == \"\" {\n353: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n354: \t}\n355: \n356: \t// Verify session exists before updating\n357: \tkey := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n358: \texistsResult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build())\n359: \tif existsResult.Error() != nil {\n360: \t\treturn existsResult.Error()\n361: \t}\n362: \n363: \texists, err := existsResult.ToInt64()\n364: \tif err != nil {\n365: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to check session existence: %w\", err)\n366: \t}\n367: \tif exists == 0 {\n368: \t\treturn ErrNotFound\n369: \t}\n370: \n371: \t// Use current time if at is zero\n372: \tif at.IsZero() {\n373: \t\tat = time.Now()\n374: \t}\n375: \n376: \t// Update the activity index\n377: \tzaddResult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().\n378: \t\tScoreMember(float64(at.Unix()), sessionID).Build())\n379: \tif zaddResult.Error() != nil {\n380: \t\treturn zaddResult.Error()\n381: \t}\n382: \n383: \treturn nil\n384: }\n385: \n386: // Close closes the Valkey connection.\n387: func (s *valkeyStore) Close() error {\n388: \ts.cli.Close()\n389: \treturn nil\n390: }\n\n(End of file - total 390 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/valkey.go","time":{"start":1775868308826,"end":1775868308854}}}}
